quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the heaven shall be rent in sunder
  84,2,"and shall obey its Lord, and shall be capable thereof"
  84,3,and when the earth shall be stretched out
  84,4,"and shall cast forth that which is therein, and shall remain empty"
  84,5,"and shall obey its Lord, and shall be capable thereof"
  84,6,"O man, verily labouring thou labourest to meet thy Lord, and thou shalt meet Him"
  84,7,And he who shall have his book given into his right hand
  84,8,shall be called to an easy account
  84,9,and shall turn unto his family with joy
  84,10,But he who shall have his book given him behind his back
  84,11,shall invoke destruction to fall upon him
  84,12,and he shall be sent into hell to be burned
  84,13,because he rejoiced insolently amidst his family on earth
  84,14,Verily he thought that he should never return unto God
  84,15,Yea verily; but his Lord beheld him
  84,16,Wherefore I swear by the redness of the sky after sun-set
  84,17,"and by the night, and the animals which it driveth together"
  84,18,and by the moon when she is at the full
  84,19,ye shall surely be transferred successively from state to state
  84,20,"What aileth them, therefore, that they believe not the resurrection"
  84,21,"and that, when the Koran is read unto them, they worship not"
  84,22,"Yea: The unbelievers accuse the same of imposture"
  84,23,But God well knoweth the malice which they keep hidden in their breasts
  84,24,Wherefore denounce unto them a grievous punishment
  84,25,"except those who believe and do good works: For them is prepared a never failing reward"
  85,1,By the heaven adorned with signs
  85,2,by the promised day of judgment
  85,3,"by the witness, and the witnessed"
  85,4,cursed were the contrivers of the pit
  85,5,of fire supplied with fuel
  85,6,when they sat round the same
  85,7,and were witnesses of what they did against the true believers
  85,8,"And they afflicted them for no other reason, but because they believed in the mighty, the glorious God"
  85,9,"unto whom belongeth the kingdom of heaven and earth: And God is witness of all things"
  85,10,"Verily for those who persecute the true believers of either sex, and afterwards repent not, is prepared the torment of hell; and they shall suffer the pain of burning"
  85,11,"But for those who believe, and do that which is right, are destined gardens beneath which rivers flow: This shall be great felicity"
  85,12,Verily the vengeance of thy Lord is severe
  85,13,"He createth, and He restoreth to life"
  85,14,"He is inclined to forgive, and gracious"
  85,15,The possessor of the glorious throne
  85,16,who effecteth that which He pleaseth
  85,17,Hath not the story of the hosts
  85,18,"of Pharaoh, and of Thamud, reached thee"
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers cease not to accuse the divine revelations of falsehood
  85,20,"But God encompasseth them behind, that they cannot escape"
  85,21,Verily that which they reject is a glorious Koran
  85,22,the original whereof is written in a table kept in heaven
  86,1,"By the heaven, and that which appeareth by night"
  86,2,But what shall cause thee to understand what that which appeareth by night is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,Every soul hath a guardian set over it
  86,5,"Let a man consider, therefore, of what he is created"
  86,6,He is created of seed poured forth
  86,7,"issuing from the loins, and the breast-bones"
  86,8,Verily God is able to restore him to life
  86,9,the day whereon all secret thoughts and actions shall be examined into
  86,10,"and he shall have no power to defend himself, nor any protector"
  86,11,By the heaven which returneth the rain
  86,12,and by the earth which openeth to let forth vegetables and springs
  86,13,Verily this is a discourse distinguishing good from evil
  86,14,and it is not composed with lightness
  86,15,Verily the infidels are laying a plot to frustrate my designs
  86,16,But I will lay a plot for their ruin
  86,17,"Wherefore, O prophet, bear with the unbelievers: Let them alone a while"